cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it using the metadata below."
title: "Scanpath Studio"
abstract: >-
  An interactive Streamlit workbench for visualizing eye-tracking-while-reading
  scanpaths: words at their true on-screen positions, fixations and saccades,
  density heatmaps, per-word reading measures, side-by-side trial comparison,
  and animated replay, all exportable as publication-ready figures.
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Omer
    family-names: Shubi
    affiliation: "LACC Lab, Technion – Israel Institute of Technology"
  - given-names: Keren
    family-names: "Gruteke Klein"
    affiliation: "LACC Lab, Technion – Israel Institute of Technology"
# NOTE: author list is provisional (a system-demo paper is in preparation).
repository-code: "https://github.com/lacclab/scanpath-studio"
url: "https://scanpath-studio.streamlit.app"
license: MIT
version: 0.14.0
date-released: "2026-06-06"
keywords:
  - eye-tracking
  - scanpath
  - visualization
  - reading
  - psycholinguistics
  - streamlit
